      "date": "2020-01-30 08:03:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlex, you are right about llog_close(), originally it is a pair for llog_open(), so I kept it mostly to keep a lot of code untouched and remains this pairing between llog_open()-llog_close()\nAs for lgh_destroyed, it is just simple replacement for lu_object_is_dying() in llog_osd_exist(). It makes this check reliable by minimal code changes.",
